For {= channel_relationship =}+ public, source-stated channel relationships between manufacturers of electronics-assembly capital equipment and channel parties serving Australia, New Zealand, Australasia, Oceania, or named Pacific territories, supply evidence for each of the {= channel_side =} channel sides listed below (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per side).

The useful work is proving the regional channel relationship from both controlled sides, not finding a seller of similar machines or collecting procurement contacts.

`channel_side` values:
- `maker_listed`: a manufacturer-owned or manufacturer-controlled page lists, names, or otherwise identifies `channel_party` for the relevant territory.
- `channel_claimed`: a channel-party-owned or channel-party-controlled page claims it represents, distributes, supplies, supports, is authorized by, or is an official partner for `manufacturer` in the relevant territory.

`channel_party` must be a distinct public channel actor such as an authorized distributor, representative, reseller, sales/service partner, or official support partner. Direct manufacturer branches, subsidiaries, same-corporate-family offices, marketplace sellers, generic used-equipment brokers, end customers, and generic component/materials distributors do not count as channel parties unless the source states a capital-equipment channel role distinct from those categories.

Requirements:
- The page must communicate that it is controlled by the side named by `channel_side`: for `maker_listed`, the manufacturer; for `channel_claimed`, the channel party. Third-party directories, industry articles, marketplace pages, press-wire republications, and similar surfaces can guide discovery but do not satisfy either controlled-side source.
- The page must identify both submitted parties: `manufacturer` and `channel_party`. Vague mentions such as "local distributor", "sales partner", or "supplier" without the named party do not count.
- The page must source-state the channel relationship at the relevant side's bar. For `maker_listed`, the manufacturer page must list, name, or identify the channel party for the territory. For `channel_claimed`, the channel-party page must claim representation, distribution, supply, support, authorization, official partnership, or a comparable equipment-channel role for the manufacturer. A logo or brand list can count only when surrounding page text makes those brands the represented or supplier set.
- The page must tie the relationship or service territory to Australia, New Zealand, Australasia, Oceania, or named Pacific territories.
- The page must show that the relationship concerns electronics-assembly capital equipment, such as SMT pick-and-place, screen printing, AOI/SPI, reflow or selective soldering, rework, dispensing/coating, component storage/handling, PCB assembly inspection, or comparable manufacturing-line equipment.
